Brent Crude Rises in London for First Time in Four Days Before ECB Meeting

-- B y   G r a n t   S m i t h
-- 
2011-05-05T07:40:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/brent-crude-rises-in-london-for-first-time-in-four-days-before-ecb-meeting.html
 Oil rose in  London  for the first time
in four days as the dollar weakened against the euro before
todayâ€™s meeting of the  European Central Bank , boosting the
appeal of commodities priced in the U.S. currency.  Brent crude for June settlement rose as much as 77 cents,
or 0.6 percent, to $121.96 a barrel and was at $121.66 at 8:35
a.m. on the ICE Futures Europe exchange in London. Oil for June
delivery on the New York Mercantile Exchange traded at $109.17 a
barrel, down 7 cents, after falling as much as 81 cents to
$108.43. The dollar fell 0.4 percent to trade at $1.4891 against
the euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
